# 20240911 next-sitemap
# public/sitemap*.xml
# public/robots.txt
#
# Intentionally commented out on 2026-03-27.
# Why: Next.js 16.2 on Vercel currently has a regression where files written to
# public/ after next build can be generated successfully during postbuild but
# still not be served in the deployed output, causing production 404s for
# sitemap.xml / sitemap-0.xml / robots.txt.
# Reference: https://github.com/vercel/next.js/issues/91864
#
# Current workaround:
# - Track public/robots.txt, public/sitemap.xml, and public/sitemap-0.xml in git.
# - Do not rely on postbuild-only generation for production serving.
#
# When routes or sitemap-worthy pages change:
# 1. Run `npm run build`
# 2. Let next-sitemap regenerate the files in public/
# 3. Commit updated public/robots.txt, public/sitemap.xml, and public/sitemap-0.xml
# 4. Deploy stable and verify the live URLs return HTTP 200 before resubmitting in GSC
#
# Revisit after the upstream regression is fixed and decide whether these files
# can safely go back to being ignored/generated-only.

